problem: If $\left(\sqrt[4]{11}\right)^{3x-3}=\frac{1}{5}$, what is the value of $\left(\sqrt[4]{11}\right)^{6x+2}$? Express your answer as a fraction.
model_solution:
Step 1: $\left(\sqrt[4]{11}\right)^{3x-3}=\frac{1}{5}$ can be rewritten as $\left(\sqrt[4]{11}\right)^{3x-3}=\left(\frac{1}{5}\right)^{1}$
Step 2: $\left(\sqrt[4]{11}\right)^{3x-3}=\left(\frac{1}{5}\right)^{1} \Rightarrow \left(\sqrt[4]{11}\right)^{3x-3}=\frac{1}{5} \Rightarrow \left( \sqrt[4]{11}\right)^{3x-3}=\left(11^{\frac{1}{4}}\right)^{3x-3}$
Step 3: $\left( \sqrt[4]{11}\right)^{3x-3}=\left(11^{\frac{1}{4}}\right)^{3x-3} \Rightarrow 11^{\frac{3x-3}{4}}=\left(11^{\frac{1}{4}}\right)^{3x-3}$
$\left(11^{\frac{1}{4}}\right)^{3x-3}=11^{\frac{3x-3}{4}} \Rightarrow (3x-3)\left(\frac{1}{4}\right)=\frac{3x-3}{4}$
$3x-3=3x-3 \Rightarrow 3x-3 \ln(11)^{\frac{3x-3}{4}}=3x-3 \ln \left(11^{\frac{1}{4}}\right)^{3x-3}$
$\frac{3x-3}{4}=\frac{1}{4} \ln \left(11^{\frac{3x-3}{4}}\right)=\frac{3x-3}{4} \ln \left(\frac{1}{5}\right)$
$\frac{1}{4} \ln \left(11^{\frac{3x-3}{4}}\right)=\frac{3x-3}{4} \ln \left(\frac{1}{5}\right) \Rightarrow \ln \left(11^{\frac{3x-3}{4}}\right)=\ln \left(\frac{1}{5}\right)^{3x-3}$
$\ln \left(11^{\frac{3x-3}{4}}\right)=\ln \left(\frac{1}{5}\right)^{3x-3} \Rightarrow 11^{\frac{3x-3}{4}}=\frac{1}{5^{3x-3}}$
$11^{\frac{3x-3}{4}}=\frac{1}{5^{3x-3}} \Rightarrow 11^{\frac{3x-3}{4}}=5^{-3(3x-3)}$
Step 4: $11^{\frac{3x-3}{4}}=5^{-3(3x-3)} \Rightarrow 11^{\frac{3x-3}{4}}=5^{-9x+9}$
